[08:26] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'note that there is a turning motion After turning the result looks very strange So I think this example demonstrates both the model\'s powerful ability (aligning the pose to the character) and its limitation When it comes to turning situations'

[08:39] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'it still cannot handle them very well This is a problem that all Wan models or indeed all open-source AI models cannot currently solve perfectly Let\'s give it an extreme challenge'

[08:51] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'For the driving video I used a beautiful woman standing on a drone constantly spinning If we look at the extracted pose it is also constantly turning The image I provided is of relatively high quality both in perspective and overall detail'

[09:05] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Therefore generating normal movements with this image should not be difficult However when it comes to the turning motion you will find that the resulting effect is completely messed up We see three arms, right?'

[09:18] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'And the turning motion cannot be accurately reflected So, under normal circumstances the overall performance of this model is excellent including its stability movement migration'

[09:30] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'and character consistency However you must be careful about a few scenarios First try to avoid props in the image While having a prop might result in a fantastic video it might also lead to some issues in the generated video'

[09:42] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'For example the one I generated earlier had an extra arm Secondly be cautious when the difference between the first frame and the pose is too significant For example'

[09:56] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the first frame is seated but the pose is standing This is prone to generating such issues However note that if you don\'t generate 176 frames but only 81 frames—completing the generation in a single sampling—this problem will not occur Finally'

[10:13] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'pay attention to the turning issue This remains an unsolved challenge for now That concludes our introduction to this model What are you waiting for? Go ahead and try it yourself Follow me and become AI savvy'
